# Auth Architecture Rules

## Staff Auth
- Staff login uses custom JWT + bcrypt
- Never replace or modify the existing staff auth system
- Staff token stored in httpOnly cookie or localStorage as "staff_token"
- Verify with src/lib/auth.ts patterns

## Player Portal Auth
- Email/password login and signup use a custom JWT flow — never next-auth credentials provider
- POST /api/public/auth/login handles email/password, returns { token, user }
- Token signed with JWT_SECRET, stored in localStorage as "player_token"
- Helper functions live in src/lib/player-auth.ts
- Protected routes check player_token and redirect to /book/login if missing

## OAuth (Google, Apple)
- Google and Apple sign-in use next-auth v5
- next-auth is ONLY used for OAuth providers — never for credentials provider
- trustHost: true must be set in the NextAuth() config
- Never add credentials provider to the NextAuth() config

## General Rules
- Never install or use next-auth credentials provider for any new auth flow
- Never use manual fetch to /api/auth/callback/credentials or /api/auth/csrf
- Never use signIn("credentials") from next-auth/react
- When adding a new login flow, follow the custom JWT pattern in src/lib/auth.ts
- Always add AUTH_SECRET and JWT_SECRET to .env.example when setting up auth
